### HTML

~~~ .code-sample.php
Minify::html($input, $comments = 2);
~~~

Minify HTML string:

~~~ .php
echo Minify::html('<!DOCTYPE html>
<html dir="ltr">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Test</title>
    <!-- remove -->
  </head>
  <body>
    <!--[if IE]> keep <[endif]-->
    <h1>Test</h1>
    <p>
      <button>Button 1</button> <button>Button 2</button>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>');
~~~

### CSS

~~~ .code-sample.php
Minify::css($input, $comments = 2);
~~~

Minify CSS string:

~~~ .php
echo Minify::css('* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font: inherit;
  -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
     -moz-box-sizing: border-box;
          box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* remove */

/*! keep */

/** keep */

html {
  background: #fff;
  font: normal normal 13px/1.5 Helmet, FreeSans, sans-serif;
  color: #000;
}');
~~~

### JS

~~~ .code-sample.php
Minify::js($input, $comments = 2);
~~~

Minify JavaScript string:

~~~ .php
echo Minify::js('var i, j, k = Date.now();

for (i = 0, j = k; i < k; ++i) {
    console.log("bark: " + i);
}');
~~~

> **Note:** The `$comments` parameter value consists of `0`, `1` and `2`:
>  - `0` means remove all comments.
>  - `1` means preserve all comments.
>  - `2` means remove all comments except special comments like IE conditional comments or license comments.